obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24501)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24501&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Arbitration and`
  line `Conciliation Act, 1996.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India:`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso and Explanation omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020,`
  line `vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
  line
  line `2. 22nd August, 1996, vide notification No. G.S.R 375(E), dated 22nd August, 1996, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24502)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24502&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) "arbitration" means any arbitration whether or not administered by permanent arbitral`
  line institution;
  line
  line `(b) "arbitration agreement" means an agreement referred to in section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) "arbitral award" includes an interim award;`
  line
  line `(d) "arbitral tribunal" means a sole arbitrator or a panel of arbitrators;`
  line
  line `^1[(e) "Court" means—`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of an arbitration other than international commercial arbitration, the principal`
  line `Civil Court of original jurisdiction in a district, and includes the High Court in exercise of its`
  line `ordinary original civil jurisdiction, having jurisdiction to decide the questions forming the`
  line `subject-matter of the arbitration if the same had been the subject-matter of a suit, but does not`
  line `include any Civil Court of a grade inferior to such principal Civil Court, or any Court of Small`
  line Causes;
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of international commercial arbitration, the High Court in exercise of its`
  line `ordinary original civil jurisdiction, having jurisdiction to decide the questions forming the`
  line `subject-matter of the arbitration if the same had been the subject-matter of a suit, and in other`
  line `cases, a High Court having jurisdiction to hear appeals from decrees of courts subordinate to that`
  line `High Court;]`
  line
  line `(f) "international commercial arbitration" means an arbitration relating to disputes arising out of`
  line `legal relationships, whether contractual or not, considered as commercial under the law in force in`
  line `India and where at least one of the parties is—`
  line
  line `(i) an individual who is a national of, or habitually resident in, any country other than India;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) a body corporate which is incorporated in any country other than India; or`
  line
  line `(iii) ^2`
  line `*** an association or a body of individuals whose central management and control is`
  line `exercised in any country other than India; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the Government of a foreign country;`
  line
  line `(g) "legal representative" means a person who in law represents the estate of a deceased person,`
  line `and includes any person who intermeddles with the estate of the deceased, and, where a party acts in a`
  line `representative character, the person on whom the estate devolves on the death of the party so acting;`
  line
  line `(h) "party" means a party to an arbitration agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) This Part shall apply where the place of arbitration is in India:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that subject to an agreement to the contrary, the provisions of sections 9, 27 and clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (1) and sub-section (3) of section 37 shall also apply to international commercial`
  line `arbitration, even if the place of arbitration is outside India, and an arbitral award made or to be made in`
  line `such place is enforceable and recognised under the provisions of Part II of this Act.]`
  line
  line `(3) This Part shall not affect any other law for the time being in force by virtue of which certain`
  line `disputes may not be submitted to arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) This Part except sub-section (1) of section 40, sections 41 and 43 shall apply to every arbitration`
  line `under any other enactment for the time being in force, as if the arbitration were pursuant to an arbitration`
  line `agreement and as if that other enactment were an arbitration agreement, except in so far as the provisions`
  line `of this Part are inconsistent with that other enactment or with any rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), and save in so far as is otherwise provided by any law`
  line `for the time being in force or in any agreement in force between India and any other country or countries,`
  line `this Part shall apply to all arbitrations and to all proceedings relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(6) Where this Part, except section 28, leaves the parties free to determine a certain issue, that`
  line `freedom shall include the right of the parties to authorise any person including an institution, to determine`
  line `that issue.`
  line
  line `(7) An arbitral award made under this Part shall be considered as a domestic award.`
  line
  line `(8) Where this Part—`
  line
  line `(a) refers to the fact that the parties have agreed or that they may agree, or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other way refers to an agreement of the parties,`
  line `that agreement shall include any arbitration rules referred to in that agreement.`
  line
  line `(9) Where this Part, other than clause (a) of section 25 or clause (a) of sub-section (2) of section 32,`
  line `refers to a claim, it shall also apply to a counterclaim, and where it refers to a defence, it shall also apply`
  line `to a defence to that counterclaim.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 2, for clause (e) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. The words "a company or" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e. f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24503)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Receipt of written communications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24503&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties,—`
  line
  line `(a) any written communication is deemed to have been received if it is delivered to the addressee`
  line `personally or at his place of business, habitual residence or mailing address, and`
  line
  line `(b) if none of the places referred to in clause (a) can be found after making a reasonable inquiry, a`
  line `written communication is deemed to have been received if it is sent to the addressee's last known`
  line `place of business, habitual residence or mailing address by registered letter or by any other means`
  line `which provides a record of the attempt to deliver it.`
  line
  line `(2) The communication is deemed to have been received on the day it is so delivered.`
  line
  line `(3) This section does not apply to written communications in respect of proceedings of any judicial`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24504)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Waiver of right to object.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24504&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `A party who knows that—`
  line
  line `(a) any provision of this Part from which the parties may derogate, or`
  line
  line `(b) any requirement under the arbitration agreement,`
  line
  line `has not been complied with and yet proceeds with the arbitration without stating his objection to such`
  line `non-compliance without undue delay or, if a time limit is provided for stating that objection, within that`
  line `period of time, shall be deemed to have waived his right to so object.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24505)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Extent of judicial intervention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24505&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, in matters governed by this Part, no judicial authority shall intervene except where so`
  line `provided in this Part.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24506)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Administrative assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24506&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `In order to facilitate the conduct of the arbitral proceedings, the`
  line `parties, or the arbitral tribunal with the consent of the parties, may arrange for administrative assistance`
  line `by a suitable institution or person.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24507)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Arbitration agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 3 (w. e. f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24507&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Part, "arbitration agreement" means an agreement by the`
  line `parties to submit to arbitration all or certain disputes which have arisen or which may arise between them`
  line `in respect of a defined legal relationship, whether contractual or not.`
  line
  line `(2) An arbitration agreement may be in the form of an arbitration clause in a contract or in the form of`
  line `a separate agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) An arbitration agreement shall be in writing.`
  line
  line `(4) An arbitration agreement is in writing if it is contained in`
  line
  line `(a) a document signed by the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) an exchange of letters, telex, telegrams or other means of telecommunication ^1[including`
  line `communication through electronic means] which provide a record of the agreement; or`
  line
  line `(c) an exchange of statements of claim and defence in which the existence of the agreement is`
  line `alleged by one party and not denied by the other.`
  line
  line `(5) The reference in a contract to a document containing an arbitration clause constitutes an`
  line `arbitration agreement if the contract is in writing and the reference is such as to make that arbitration`
  line `clause part of the contract.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24508)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to refer parties to arbitration where there is an arbitration agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24508&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A`
  line `judicial authority, before which an action is brought in a matter which is the subject of an arbitration`
  line `agreement shall, if a party to the arbitration agreement or any person claiming through or under him, so`
  line `applies not later than the date of submitting his first statement on the substance of the dispute, then,`
  line `notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of the Supreme Court or any Court, refer the parties to`
  line `arbitration unless it finds that prima facie no valid arbitration agreement exists.]`
  line
  line `(2) The application referred to in sub-section (1) shall not be entertained unless it is accompanied by`
  line `the original arbitration agreement or a duly certified copy thereof:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that where the original arbitration agreement or a certified copy thereof is not available`
  line `with the party applying for reference to arbitration under sub-section (1), and the said agreement or`
  line `certified copy is retained by the other party to that agreement, then, the party so applying shall file such`
  line `application along with a copy of the arbitration agreement and a petition praying the Court to call upon`
  line `the other party to produce the original arbitration agreement or its duly certified copy before that Court.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding that an application has been made under sub-section (1) and that the issue is`
  line `pending before the judicial authority, an arbitration may be commenced or continued and an arbitral`
  line `award made.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Insertion of section 8A and section 8B.--After section 8, insert the following sections, namely:--`
  line
  line `"8A. Power of the court, seized of petitions under sections 9 or 11 of the Act, to refer the`
  line `dispute to Mediation or Conciliation.--(1) If during the pendency of petitions under sections 9 or`
  line `11 of the Act, it appears to the court, that there exists elements of a settlement which may be`
  line `acceptable to the parties, the court may, with the consent of parties, refer the parties, for resolution of`
  line `their disputes, to,--`
  line
  line `(a) mediation; or`
  line
  line `(b) conciliation.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for reference of a dispute to mediation is as under--`
  line
  line `(a) where a dispute has been referred for resolution by recourse to mediation, the procedure`
  line `framed under that Act shall apply;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of a successful resolution of the dispute, the Mediator shall immediately forward`
  line `the mediated settlement to the referral court;`
  line
  line `(c) on receipt of the mediated settlement, the referral court shall independently apply its`
  line `judicial mind and record a satisfaction that the mediated settlement is genuine, lawful, voluntary,`
  line `entered into without coercion, undue influence, fraud or misrepresentation and that there is no`
  line `other legal impediment in accepting the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the court shall record a statement on oath of the parties, or their authorised`
  line `representatives, affirming the mediated settlement as well as a clear undertaking of the parties to`
  line `abide by the terms of the settlement;`
  line
  line `(e) if satisfied, the court shall pass an order in terms of the settlement;`
  line
  line `(f) if the main petition, in which the reference was made is pending, it shall be disposed of by`
  line `the referral court in terms thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) if the main petition, in which the reference was made stands disposed of, the mediated`
  line `settlement and the matter shall be listed before the referral court, which shall pass orders in`
  line `accordance with clauses (iii), (iv) and (v);`
  line
  line `(h) such a mediated settlement, shall have the same status and effect as an arbitral award and`
  line `may be enforced in the manner specified under section 36 of the Act.`
  line
  line `(3) With respect to reference of a dispute to conciliation, the provisions of Part II of this Act shall`
  line `apply as if the conciliation proceedings were initiated by the parties under the relevant provision of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `8B. Power of the court, seized of matters under sections 34 or 37 of the Act, to refer the`
  line `dispute to Mediation or Conciliation.--(1) If during the pendency of a petition under section 34 or`
  line `an appeal under section 37 of the Act, it appears to the court, that there exists elements of a settlement`
  line `which may be acceptable to the parties, the court may, with the consent of parties, refer the parties,`
  line `for resolution of their disputes, to:--`
  line
  line `(a) mediation; or`
  line
  line `(b) conciliation.`
  line
  line `(2) The procedure for reference of a dispute to mediation is as under:--`
  line
  line `(a) where a dispute has been referred for resolution by recourse to mediation, the procedure`
  line `framed under the Act shall apply;`
  line
  line `(b) in case of a successful resolution of the dispute, the Mediator shall immediately forward`
  line `the mediated settlement to the referral court;`
  line
  line `(c) on receipt of the mediated settlement, the referral court shall independently apply its`
  line `judicial mind and record a satisfaction that the mediated settlement is genuine, lawful,`
  line `voluntary, entered into without coercion, undue influence, fraud or misrepresentation and that`
  line `there is no other legal impediment in accepting the same;`
  line
  line `(d) the court shall record a statement on oath of the parties, or their authorized`
  line `representatives, affirming the mediated settlement, a clear undertaking of the parties to abide by`
  line `the terms of the settlement as well as statement to the above effect;`
  line
  line `(e) if satisfied, the court shall pass an order in terms of the settlement;`
  line
  line `(f) if the main petition, in which the reference was made is pending, it shall be disposed of`
  line `by the referral court in terms thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) if the main petition, in which the reference was made stands disposed of, the mediated`
  line `settlement and the matter shall be listed before the referral court, which shall pass orders in`
  line `accordance with clauses (iii), (iv) and (v);`
  line
  line `(h) such a mediated settlement, shall have the status of a modified arbitral award and may`
  line `be enforced in the manner specified under section 36 of the Act.`
  line
  line `(3) With respect to reference of a dispute to conciliation, the provisions of Part III of the Act,`
  line `shall apply as if the conciliation proceedings were initiated by the parties under the relevant provision`
  line `of this Act."`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w. e. f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24509)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Interim measures, etc., by Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24509&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] A party may, before or during arbitral proceedings or at`
  line `any time after the making of the arbitral award but before it is enforced in accordance with section 36,`
  line `apply to a court—`
  line
  line `(i) for the appointment of a guardian for a minor or person of unsound mind for the purposes of`
  line `arbitral proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for an interim measure of protection in respect of any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the preservation, interim custody or sale of any goods which are the subject-matter of the`
  line `arbitration agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) securing the amount in dispute in the arbitration;`
  line
  line `(c) the detention, preservation or inspection of any property or thing which is the`
  line `subject-matter of the dispute in arbitration, or as to which any question may arise therein and`
  line `authorising for any of the aforesaid purposes any person to enter upon any land or building in the`
  line `possession of any party, or authorising any samples to be taken or any observation to be made, or`
  line `experiment to be tried, which may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of obtaining full`
  line `information or evidence;`
  line
  line `(d) interim injunction or the appointment of a receiver;`
  line
  line `(e) such other interim measure of protection as may appear to the Court to be just and`
  line convenient,
  line
  line `and the Court shall have the same power for making orders as it has for the purpose of, and in relation`
  line `to, any proceedings before it.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where, before the commencement of the arbitral proceedings, a Court passes an order for any`
  line `interim measure of protection under sub-section (1), the arbitral proceedings shall be commenced within a`
  line `period of ninety days from the date of such order or within such further time as the Court may determine.`
  line
  line `(3) Once the arbitral tribunal has been constituted, the Court shall not entertain an application under`
  line `sub-section (1), unless the Court finds that circumstances exist which may not render the remedy provided`
  line `under section 17 efficacious.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 9 shall be renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24510)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Number of arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24510&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The parties are free to determine the number of arbitrators,`
  line `provided that such number shall not be an even number.`
  line
  line `(2) Failing the determination referred to in sub-section (1), the arbitral tribunal shall consist of a sole`
  line arbitrator.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24511)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appointment of arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24511&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person of any nationality may be an arbitrator, unless`
  line `otherwise agreed by the parties.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to sub-section (6), the parties are free to agree on a procedure for appointing the arbitrator`
  line `or arbitrators.`
  line
  line `(3) Failing any agreement referred to in sub-section (2), in an arbitration with three arbitrators, each`
  line `party shall appoint one arbitrator, and the two appointed arbitrators shall appoint the third arbitrator who`
  line `shall act as the presiding arbitrator.`
  line
  line `(4) If the appointment procedure in sub-section (3) applies and—`
  line
  line `(a) a party fails to appoint an arbitrator within thirty days from the receipt of a request to do so`
  line `from the other party; or`
  line
  line `(b) the two appointed arbitrators fail to agree on the third arbitrator within thirty days from the`
  line `date of their appointment,`
  line
  line `the appointment shall be made, upon request of a party, by ^1[the Supreme Court or, as the case may be,`
  line `the High Court or any person or institution designated by such Court];`
  line
  line `(5) Failing any agreement referred to in sub-section (2), in an arbitration with a sole arbitrator, if the`
  line `parties fail to agree on the arbitrator within thirty days from receipt of a request by one party from the`
  line `other party to so agree the appointment shall be made, upon request of a party, by ^1[the Supreme Court or,`
  line `as the case may be, the High Court or any person or institution designated by such Court].`
  line
  line `(6) Where, under an appointment procedure agreed upon by the parties,—`
  line
  line `(a) a party fails to act as required under that procedure; or`
  line
  line `(b) the parties, or the two appointed arbitrators, fail to reach an agreement expected of them under`
  line `that procedure; or`
  line
  line `(c) a person, including an institution, fails to perform any function entrusted to him or it under`
  line `that procedure,`
  line
  line `a party may request ^1[the Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the High Court or any person or`
  line `institution designated by such Court] to take the necessary measure, unless the agreement on the`
  line `appointment procedure provides other means for securing the appointment.`
  line
  line `^2[(6A) The Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the High Court, while considering any application`
  line `under sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) or sub-section (6), shall, notwithstanding any judgment, decree or`
  line `order of any Court, confine to the examination of the existence of an arbitration agreement.`
  line
  line `(6B) The designation of any person or institution by the Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the`
  line `High Court, for the purposes of this section shall not be regarded as a delegation of judicial power by the`
  line `Supreme Court or the High Court.]`
  line
  line `(7) A decision on a matter entrusted by sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) or sub-section (6) to ^3[the`
  line `Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the High Court or the person or institution designated by such`
  line `Court is final and no appeal including Letters Patent Appeal shall lie against such decision].`
  line
  line ^4
  line `(8) The Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the High Court or the person or institution designated`
  line `by such Court, before appointing an arbitrator, shall seek a disclosure in writing from the prospective`
  line `arbitrator in terms of sub-section (1) of section 12, and have due regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) any qualifications required for the arbitrator by the agreement of the parties; and`
  line
  line `(b) the contents of the disclosure and other considerations as are likely to secure the appointment`
  line `of an independent and impartial arbitrator.]`
  line
  line `(9) In the case of appointment of sole or third arbitrator in an international commercial arbitration,`
  line `^5[the Supreme Court or the person or institution designated by that Court] may appoint an arbitrator of a`
  line `nationality other than the nationalities of the parties where the parties belong to different nationalities.`
  line
  line `^6[(10) The Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the High Court, may make such scheme as the said`
  line `Court may deem appropriate for dealing with matters entrusted by sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) or`
  line `sub-section (6), to it.]`
  line
  line `(11) Where more than one request has been made under sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) or`
  line `sub-section (6) to the Chief Justices of different High Courts or their designates, ^7[different High Courts`
  line `or their designates, the High Court or its designate to whom the request has been first made] under the`
  line `relevant sub-section shall alone be competent to decide on the request.`
  line
  line `^8[(12) (a) Where the matters referred to in sub-sections (4), (5), (6), (7), (8) and sub-section (10) arise`
  line `in an international commercial arbitration, the reference to the "Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the`
  line `High Court" in those sub-sections shall be construed as a reference to the "Supreme Court"; and`
  line
  line `(b) Where the matters referred to in sub-sections (4), (5), (6), (7), (8) and sub-section (10) arise in any`
  line `other arbitration, the reference to the Supreme Court or, as the case may be, the High Court in those`
  line `sub-sections shall be construed as a reference to the "High Court" within whose local limits the principal`
  line `Civil Court referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2 is situate, and where the High Court`
  line `itself is the Court referred to in that clause, to that High Court.]`
  line
  line `^9[(13) An application made under this section for appointment of an arbitrator or arbitrators shall be`
  line `disposed of by the Supreme Court or the High Court or the person or institution designated by such Court,`
  line `as the case may be, as expeditiously as possible and an endeavour shall be made to dispose of the matter`
  line `within a period of sixty days from the date of service of notice on the opposite party.`
  line
  line `(14) For the purpose of determination of the fees of the arbitral tribunal and the manner of its`
  line `payment to the arbitral tribunal, the High Court may frame such rules as may be necessary, after taking`
  line `into consideration the rates specified in the Fourth Schedule.`
  line
  line Explanation.—
  line `For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that this sub-section shall not apply to`
  line `international commercial arbitration and in arbitrations (other than international commercial arbitration)`
  line `in case where parties have agreed for determination of fees as per the rules of an arbitral institution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 6, for "the Chief Justice or any person or institution designated by him" (w. e. f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 6,ibid., for "the Chief Justice or the person or institution designated by him is final" (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 6, for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "the Chief Justice of India of India or the person or institution designated by him" (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (10) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 6,ibid., for "the Chief Justices of different High Courts or their designates, the Chief Justice or his designate to`
  line `whom the request has been first made" (w.e.f 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (12) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (24512)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Central Government to amend Fourth Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24512&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Power of Central Government to amend Fourth Schedule.—(1) If the Central Government`
  line `Government is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, amend the Fourth Schedule and thereupon the Fourth Schedule shall be deemed to have been`
  line `amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `disapproving the issue of the notification or both Houses agree in making any modification in the notification, the notification shall not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by the both Houses of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24513)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Grounds for challenge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24513&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) When a person is approached in connection with his possible`
  line `appointment as an arbitrator, he shall disclose in writing any circumstances,—`
  line
  line `(a) such as the existence either direct or indirect, of any past or present relationship with or`
  line `interest in any of the parties or in relation to the subject-matter in dispute, whether financial, business,`
  line `professional or other kind, which is likely to give rise to justifiable doubts as to his independence or`
  line `impartiality; and`
  line
  line `(b) which are likely to affect his ability to devote sufficient time to the arbitration and in`
  line `particular his ability to complete the entire arbitration within a period of twelve months.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.—The grounds stated in the Fifth Schedule shall guide in determining whether`
  line `circumstances exist which give rise to justifiable doubts as to the independence or impartiality of an`
  line arbitrator.
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—The disclosure shall be made by such person in the form specified in the Sixth`
  line Schedule.]
  line
  line `(3) An arbitrator may be challenged only if—`
  line
  line `(a) circumstances exist that give rise to justifiable doubts as to his independence or impartiality,`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) he does not possess the qualifications agreed to by the parties.`
  line
  line `(4) A party may challenge an arbitrator appointed by him, or in whose appointment he has`
  line `participated, only for reasons of which he becomes aware after the appointment has been made.`
  line
  line `^2[(5) Notwithstanding any prior agreement to the contrary, any person whose relationship, with the`
  line `parties or counsel or the subject-matter of the dispute, falls under any of the categories specified in the`
  line `Seventh Schedule shall be ineligible to be appointed as an arbitrator:`
  line
  line `Provided that parties may, subsequent to disputes having arisen between them, waive the applicability`
  line `of this sub-section by an express agreement in writing.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 8, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24514)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Challenge procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24514&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to sub-section (4), the parties are free to agree on a procedure`
  line `for challenging an arbitrator.`
  line
  line `(2) Failing any agreement referred to in sub-section (1), a party who intends to challenge an arbitrator`
  line `shall, within fifteen days after becoming aware of the constitution of the arbitral tribunal or after`
  line `becoming aware of any circumstances referred to in sub-section (3) of section 12, send a written`
  line `statement of the reasons for the challenge to the arbitral tribunal.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless the arbitrator challenged under sub-section (2) withdraws from his office or the other party`
  line `agrees to the challenge, the arbitral tribunal shall decide on the challenge.`
  line
  line `(4) If a challenge under any procedure agreed upon by the parties or under the procedure under`
  line `sub-section (2) is not successful, the arbitral tribunal shall continue the arbitral proceedings and make an`
  line `arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an arbitral award is made under sub-section (4), the party challenging the arbitrator may`
  line `make an application for setting aside such an arbitral award in accordance with section 34.`
  line
  line `(6) Where an arbitral award is set aside on an application made under sub-section (5), the Court may`
  line `decide as to whether the arbitrator who is challenged is entitled to any fees.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24515)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Failure or impossibility to act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "The mandate of an arbitrator shall terminate if" (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24515&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `^1[The mandate of an arbitrator shall terminate and he shall`
  line `be substituted by another arbitrator, if]—`
  line
  line `(a) he becomes de jure or de facto unable to perform his functions or for other reasons fails to act`
  line `without undue delay; and`
  line
  line `(b) he withdraws from his office or the parties agree to the termination of his mandate.`
  line
  line `(2) If a controversy remains concerning any of the grounds referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1),`
  line `a party may, unless otherwise agreed by the parties, apply to the Court to decide on the termination of the`
  line mandate.
  line
  line `(3) If, under this section or sub-section (3) of section 13, an arbitrator withdraws from his office or a`
  line `party agrees to the termination of the mandate of an arbitrator, it shall not imply acceptance of the validity`
  line `of any ground referred to in this section or sub-section (3) of section 12.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24516)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Termination of mandate and substitution of arbitrator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24516&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) In addition to the circumstances`
  line `referred to in section 13 or section 14, the mandate of an arbitrator shall terminate—`
  line
  line `(a) where he withdraws from office for any reason; or`
  line
  line `(b) by or pursuant to agreement of the parties.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the mandate of an arbitrator terminates, a substitute arbitrator shall be appointed according`
  line `to the rules that were applicable to the appointment of the arbitrator being replaced.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, where an arbitrator is replaced under sub-section (2), any`
  line `hearings previously held may be repeated at the discretion of the arbitral tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, an order or ruling of the arbitral tribunal made prior to the`
  line `replacement of an arbitrator under this section shall not be invalid solely because there has been a change`
  line `in the composition of the arbitral tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24517)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Competence of arbitral tribunal to rule on its jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24517&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The arbitral tribunal may rule`
  line `on its own jurisdiction, including ruling on any objections with respect to the existence or validity of the`
  line `arbitration agreement, and for that purpose,—`
  line
  line `(a) an arbitration clause which forms part of a contract shall be treated as an agreement`
  line `independent of the other terms of the contract; and`
  line
  line `(b) a decision by the arbitral tribunal that the contract is null and void shall not entail ipso jure the`
  line `invalidity of the arbitration clause.`
  line
  line `(2) A plea that the arbitral tribunal does not have jurisdiction shall be raised not later than the`
  line `submission of the statement of defence; however, a party shall not be precluded from raising such a plea`
  line `merely because that he has appointed, or participated in the appointment of, an arbitrator.`
  line
  line `(3) A plea that the arbitral tribunal is exceeding the scope of its authority shall be raised as soon as the`
  line `matter alleged to be beyond the scope of its authority is raised during the arbitral proceedings.`
  line
  line `(4) The arbitral tribunal may, in either of the cases referred to in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3),`
  line `admit a later plea if it considers the delay justified.`
  line
  line `(5) The arbitral tribunal shall decide on a plea referred to in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) and,`
  line `where the arbitral tribunal takes a decision rejecting the plea, continue with the arbitral proceedings and`
  line `make an arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(6) A party aggrieved by such an arbitral award may make an application for setting aside such an`
  line `arbitral award in accordance with section 34.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24518)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Interim measures ordered by arbitral tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24518&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `^1[17. Interim measures ordered by arbitral tribunal.-- (1) A party may, during the arbitral`
  line `proceedings ^2***, apply to the arbitral tribunal--`
  line
  line `(i) for the appointment of a guardian for a minor or person of unsound mind for the purposes of`
  line `arbitral proceedings; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for an interim measure of protection in respect of any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the preservation, interim custody or sale of any goods which are the subject-matter of the`
  line `arbitration agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) securing the amount in dispute in the arbitration;`
  line
  line `(c) the detention, preservation or inspection of any property or thing which is the`
  line `subject-matter of the dispute in arbitration, or as to which any question may arise therein and`
  line `authorising for any of the aforesaid purposes any person to enter upon any land or building in the`
  line `possession of any party, or authorising any samples to be taken, or any observation to be made, or`
  line `experiment to be tried, which may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of obtaining full`
  line `information or evidence;`
  line
  line `(d) interim injunction or the appointment of a receiver;`
  line
  line `(e) such other interim measure of protection as may appear to the arbitral tribunal to be just`
  line `and convenient,`
  line `and the arbitral tribunal shall have the same power for making orders, as the court has for the purpose of,`
  line `and in relation to, any proceedings before it.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any orders passed in an appeal under section 37, any order issued by the arbitral`
  line `tribunal under this section shall be deemed to be an order of the Court for all purposes and shall be`
  line `enforceable under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in the same manner as if it were an`
  line `order of the Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 10, for section 17 (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "or at any time after the making of the arbitral award but before it is enforced in accordance with`
  line `section 36" omitted by Act 33 of 2019, s. 4 (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24519)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Equal treatment of parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24519&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The parties shall be treated with equality and each party shall be`
  line `given a full opportunity to present his case.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24520)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Determination of rules of procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24520&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The arbitral tribunal shall not be bound by the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to this Part, the parties are free to agree on the procedure to be followed by the arbitral`
  line `tribunal in conducting its proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) Failing any agreement referred to in sub-section (2), the arbitral tribunal may, subject to this Part,`
  line `conduct the proceedings in the manner it considers appropriate.`
  line
  line `(4) The power of the arbitral tribunal under sub-section (3) includes the power to determine the`
  line `admissibility, relevance, materiality and weight of any evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24521)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Place of arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24521&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The parties are free to agree on the place of arbitration.`
  line
  line `(2) Failing any agreement referred to in sub-section (1), the place of arbitration shall be determined`
  line `by the arbitral tribunal having regard to the circumstances of the case, including the convenience of the`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the arbitral tribunal may, unless otherwise`
  line `agreed by the parties, meet at any place it considers appropriate for consultation among its members, for`
  line `hearing witnesses, experts or the parties, or for inspection of documents, goods or other property.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24522)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Commencement of arbitral proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24522&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, the arbitral`
  line `proceedings in respect of a particular dispute commence on the date on which a request for that dispute to`
  line `be referred to arbitration is received by the respondent.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24523)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title Language.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24523&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The parties are free to agree upon the language or languages to be used in the`
  line `arbitral proceedings.`
  line
  line `(2) Failing any agreement referred to in sub-section (1), the arbitral tribunal shall determine the`
  line `language or languages to be used in the arbitral proceedings.`
  line
  line `(3) The agreement or determination, unless otherwise specified, shall apply to any written statement`
  line `by a party, any hearing and any arbitral award, decision or other communication by the arbitral tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) The arbitral tribunal may order that any documentary evidence shall be accompanied by a`
  line `translation into the language or languages agreed upon by the parties or determined by the arbitral`
  line tribunal.
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24524)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Statements of claim and defence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24524&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Within the period of time agreed upon by the parties or`
  line `determined by the arbitral tribunal, the claimant shall state the facts supporting his claim, the points at`
  line `issue and the relief or remedy sought, and the respondent shall state his defence in respect of these`
  line `particulars, unless the parties have otherwise agreed as to the required elements of those statements.`
  line
  line `(2) The parties may submit with their statements all documents they consider to be relevant or may`
  line `add a reference to the documents or other evidence they will submit.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) The respondent, in support of his case, may also submit a counterclaim or plead a set-off,`
  line `which shall be adjudicated upon by the arbitral tribunal, if such counterclaim or set-off falls within the`
  line `scope of the arbitration agreement.]`
  line
  line `(3) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, either party may amend or supplement his claim or`
  line `defence during the course of the arbitral proceedings, unless the arbitral tribunal considers it inappropriate`
  line `to allow the amendment or supplement having regard to the delay in making it.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The statement of claim and defence under this section shall be completed within a period of six`
  line `months from the date the arbitrator or all the arbitrators, as the case may be, received notice, in writing of`
  line `their appointment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 11 (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 5 (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24525)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Hearings and written proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24525&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, the arbitral`
  line `tribunal shall decide whether to hold oral hearings for the presentation of evidence or for oral argument,`
  line `or whether the proceedings shall be conducted on the basis of documents and other materials:`
  line
  line `Provided that the arbitral tribunal shall hold oral hearings, at an appropriate stage of the proceedings,`
  line `on a request by a party, unless the parties have agreed that no oral hearing shall be held:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that the arbitral tribunal shall, as far as possible, hold oral hearings for the`
  line `presentation of evidence or for oral argument on day-to-day basis, and not grant any adjournments unless`
  line `sufficient cause is made out, and may impose costs including exemplary costs on the party seeking`
  line `adjournment without any sufficient cause.]`
  line
  line `(2) The parties shall be given sufficient advance notice of any hearing and of any meeting of the`
  line `arbitral tribunal for the purposes of inspection of documents, goods or other property.`
  line
  line `(3) All statements, documents or other information supplied to, or applications made to the arbitral`
  line `tribunal by one party shall be communicated to the other party, and any expert report or evidentiary`
  line `document on which the arbitral tribunal may rely in making its decision shall be communicated to the`
  line parties.
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24526)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Default of a party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 13, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24526&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, where, without showing sufficient`
  line cause,—
  line
  line `(a) the claimant fails to communicate his statement of claim in accordance with sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 23, the arbitral tribunal shall terminate the proceedings;`
  line
  line `(b) the respondent fails to communicate his statement of defence in accordance with`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 23, the arbitral tribunal shall continue the proceedings without treating that`
  line `failure in itself as an admission of the allegations by the claimant ^1[and shall have the discretion to`
  line `treat the right of the respondent to file such statement of defence as having been forfeited].`
  line
  line `(c) a party fails to appear at an oral hearing or to produce documentary evidence, the arbitral`
  line `tribunal may continue the proceedings and make the arbitral award on the evidence before it.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24527)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Expert appointed by arbitral tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24527&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, the arbitral`
  line `tribunal may—`
  line
  line `(a) appoint one or more experts to report to it on specific issues to be determined by the arbitral`
  line `tribunal, and`
  line
  line `(b) require a party to give the expert any relevant information or to produce, or to provide access`
  line `to, any relevant documents, goods or other property for his inspection.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, if a party so requests or if the arbitral tribunal considers it`
  line `necessary, the expert shall, after delivery of his written or oral report, participate in an oral hearing where`
  line `the parties have the opportunity to put questions to him and to present expert witnesses in order to testify`
  line `on the points at issue.`
  line
  line `(3) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, the expert shall, on the request of a party, make available`
  line `to that party for examination all documents, goods or other property in the possession of the expert with`
  line `which he was provided in order to prepare his report.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (24528)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Court assistance in taking evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24528&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The arbitral tribunal, or a party with the approval of`
  line `the arbitral tribunal, may apply to the Court for assistance in taking evidence.`
  line
  line `(2) The application shall specify—`
  line
  line `(a) the names and addresses of the parties and the arbitrators;`
  line
  line `(b) the general nature of the claim and the relief sought;`
  line
  line `(c) the evidence to be obtained, in particular,—`
  line
  line `(i) the name and address of any person to be heard as witness or expert witness and a`
  line `statement of the subject-matter of the testimony required;`
  line
  line `(ii) the description of any document to be produced or property to be inspected.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court may, within its competence and according to its rules on taking evidence, execute the`
  line `request by ordering that the evidence be provided directly to the arbitral tribunal.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court may, while making an order under sub-section (3), issue the same processes to`
  line `witnesses as it may issue in suits tried before it.`
  line
  line `(5) Persons failing to attend in accordance with such process, or making any other default, or refusing`
  line `to give their evidence, or guilty of any contempt to the arbitral tribunal during the conduct of arbitral`
  line `proceedings, shall be subject to the like disadvantages, penalties and punishments by order of the Court`
  line `on the representation of the arbitral tribunal as they would incur for the like offences in suits tried before`
  line `the Court.`
  line
  line `(6) In this section the expression "Processes" includes summonses and commissions for the`
  line `examination of witnesses and summonses to produce documents.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (24529)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Rules applicable to substance of dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 14, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24529&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the place of arbitration is situate in`
  line India,—
  line
  line `(a) in an arbitration other than an international commercial arbitration, the arbitral tribunal shall`
  line `decide the dispute submitted to arbitration in accordance with the substantive law for the time being`
  line `in force in India;`
  line
  line `(b) in international commercial arbitration,—`
  line
  line `(i) the arbitral tribunal shall decide the dispute in accordance with the rules of law designated`
  line `by the parties as applicable to the substance of the dispute;`
  line
  line `(ii) any designation by the parties of the law or legal system of a given country shall be`
  line `construed, unless otherwise expressed, as directly referring to the substantive law of that country`
  line `and not to its conflict of laws rules;`
  line
  line `(iii) failing any designation of the law under clause (a) by the parties, the arbitral tribunal`
  line `shall apply the rules of law it considers to be appropriate given all the circumstances surrounding`
  line `the dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) The arbitral tribunal shall decide ex aequo et bono or as amiable compositeur only if the parties`
  line `have expressly authorised it to do so.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) While deciding and making an award, the arbitral tribunal shall, in all cases, take into account`
  line `the terms of the contract and trade usages applicable to the transaction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (24530)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Decision making by panel of arbitrators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24530&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, in`
  line `arbitral proceedings with more than one arbitrator, any decision of the arbitral tribunal shall be made by a`
  line `majority of all its members.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding sub-section (1), if authorised by the parties or all the members of the arbitral`
  line `tribunal, questions of procedure may be decided by the presiding arbitrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (24531)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 31
  title `Time limit for arbitral award.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24531&sectionno=29A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A.Time limit for arbitral award.--^2[(1) The award in matters other than international`
  line `commercial arbitration shall be made by the arbitral tribunal within a period of twelve months from the`
  line `date of completion of pleadings under sub-section (4) of section 23:`
  line
  line `Provided that the award in the matter of international commercial arbitration may be made as`
  line `expeditiously as possible and endeavor may be made to dispose of the matter within a period of twelve`
  line `months from the date of completion of pleadings under sub-section (4) of section 23.]`
  line
  line `(2) If the award is made within a period of six months from the date the arbitral tribunal enters upon`
  line `the reference, the arbitral tribunal shall be entitled to receive such amount of additional fees as the parties`
  line `may agree.`
  line
  line `(3) The parties may, by consent, extend the period specified in sub-section (1) for making award for a`
  line `further period not exceeding six months.`
  line
  line `(4) If the award is not made within the period specified in sub-section (1) or the extended period`
  line `specified under sub-section (3), the mandate of the arbitrator(s) shall terminate unless the Court has,`
  line `either prior to or after the expiry of the period so specified, extended the period:`
  line
  line `Provided that while extending the period under this sub-section, if the Court finds that the`
  line `proceedings have been delayed for the reasons attributable to the arbitral tribunal, then, it may order`
  line `reduction of fees of arbitrator(s) by not exceeding five per cent. for each month of such delay.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that where an application under sub-section (5) is pending, the mandate of the`
  line `arbitrator shall continue till the disposal of the said application:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the arbitrator shall be given an opportunity of being heard before the fees is`
  line reduced.]
  line
  line `(5) The extension of period referred to in sub-section (4) may be on the application of any of the`
  line `parties and may be granted only for sufficient cause and on such terms and conditions as may be imposed`
  line `by the Court.`
  line
  line `(6) While extending the period referred to in sub-section (4), it shall be open to the Court to substitute`
  line `one or all of the arbitrators and if one or all of the arbitrators are substituted, the arbitral proceedings shall`
  line `continue from the stage already reached and on the basis of the evidence and material already on record,`
  line `and the arbitrator(s) appointed under this section shall be deemed to have received the said evidence and`
  line material.
  line
  line `(7) In the event of arbitrator(s) being appointed under this section, the arbitral tribunal thus`
  line `reconstituted shall be deemed to be in continuation of the previously appointed arbitral tribunal.`
  line
  line `(8) It shall be open to the Court to impose actual or exemplary costs upon any of the parties under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `(9) An application filed under sub-section (5) shall be disposed of by the Court as expeditiously as`
  line `possible and endeavour shall be made to dispose of the matter within a period of sixty days from the date`
  line `of service of notice on the opposite party.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Amendment of sections 29A.--`
  line `(a) for sub-section (1), the following sub-section shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(1) The award shall be made within a period of twelve months from the date the arbitral tribunal`
  line `enters upon the reference.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, an arbitral tribunal shall be deemed to have`
  line `entered upon the reference on the date on which the arbitrator or all the arbitrators, as the case may`
  line `be, have received notice, in writing, of their appointment.";`
  line
  line `(b) in sub-section (4), omit second and third provisos.`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 15 (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 6, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (24532)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 32
  title `Fast track procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 15, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24532&sectionno=29B&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[29B. Fast track procedure.-- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the parties to an`
  line `arbitration agreement, may, at any stage either before or at the time of appointment of the arbitral tribunal,`
  line `agree in writing to have their dispute resolved by fast track procedure specified in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(2) The parties to the arbitration agreement, while agreeing for resolution of dispute by fast track`
  line `procedure, may agree that the arbitral tribunal shall consist of a sole arbitrator who shall be chosen by the`
  line parties.
  line
  line `(3) The arbitral tribunal shall follow the following procedure while conducting arbitration`
  line `proceedings under sub-section (1):--`
  line
  line `(a) The arbitral tribunal shall decide the dispute on the basis of written pleadings, documents and`
  line `submissions filed by the parties without any oral hearing;`
  line
  line `(b) The arbitral tribunal shall have power to call for any further information or clarification from`
  line `the parties in addition to the pleadings and documents filed by them;`
  line
  line `(c) An oral hearing may be held only, if, all the parties make a request or if the arbitral tribunal`
  line `considers it necessary to have oral hearing for clarifying certain issues;`
  line
  line `(d) The arbitral tribunal may dispense with any technical formalities, if an oral hearing is held,`
  line `and adopt such procedure as deemed appropriate for expeditious disposal of the case.`
  line
  line `(4) The award under this section shall be made within a period of six months from the date the arbitral`
  line `tribunal enters upon the reference.`
  line
  line `(5) If the award is not made within the period specified in sub-section (4), the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (3) to (9) of section 29A shall apply to the proceedings.`
  line
  line `(6) The fees payable to the arbitrator and the manner of payment of the fees shall be such as may be`
  line `agreed between the arbitrator and the parties.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (24533)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 33
  title Settlement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24533&sectionno=30&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) It is not incompatible with an arbitration agreement for an arbitral tribunal to`
  line `encourage settlement of the dispute and, with the agreement of the parties, the arbitral tribunal may use`
  line `mediation, conciliation or other procedures at any time during the arbitral proceedings to encourage`
  line settlement.
  line
  line `(2) If, during arbitral proceedings, the parties settle the dispute, the arbitral tribunal shall terminate the`
  line `proceedings and, if requested by the parties and not objected to by the arbitral tribunal, record the`
  line `settlement in the form of an arbitral award on agreed terms.`
  line
  line `(3) An arbitral award on agreed terms shall be made in accordance with section 31 and shall state that`
  line `it is an arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(4) An arbitral award on agreed terms shall have the same status and effect as any other arbitral award`
  line `on the substance of the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (24534)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 34
  title `Form and contents of arbitral award.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24534&sectionno=31&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) An arbitral award shall be made in writing and shall`
  line `be signed by the members of the arbitral tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1), in arbitral proceedings with more than one arbitrator, the`
  line `signatures of the majority of all the members of the arbitral tribunal shall be sufficient so long as the`
  line `reason for any omitted signature is stated.`
  line
  line `(3) The arbitral award shall state the reasons upon which it is based, unless—`
  line
  line `(a) the parties have agreed that no reasons are to be given, or`
  line
  line `(b) the award is an arbitral award on agreed terms under section 30.`
  line
  line `(4) The arbitral award shall state its date and the place of arbitration as determined in accordance with`
  line `section 20 and the award shall be deemed to have been made at that place.`
  line
  line `(5) After the arbitral award is made, a signed copy shall be delivered to each party.`
  line
  line `(6) The arbitral tribunal may, at any time during the arbitral proceedings, make an interim arbitral`
  line `award on any matter with respect to which it may make a final arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, where and in so far as an arbitral award is for the`
  line `payment of money, the arbitral tribunal may include in the sum for which the award is made interest, at`
  line `such rate as it deems reasonable, on the whole or any part of the money, for the whole or any part of the`
  line `period between the date on which the cause of action arose and the date on which the award is made.`
  line
  line `^1[(b) A sum directed to be paid by an arbitral award shall, unless the award otherwise directs, carry`
  line `interest at the rate of two per cent. higher than the current rate of interest prevalent on the date of award,`
  line `from the date of award to the date of payment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—The expression "current rate of interest" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it`
  line `under clause (b) of section 2 of the Interest Act, 1978 (14 of 1978).]`
  line
  line `^2[(8) The costs of an arbitration shall be fixed by the arbitral tribunal in accordance with section 31A.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of clause (a), "costs" means reasonable costs relating to—`
  line
  line `(i) the fees and expenses of the arbitrators and witnesses,`
  line
  line `(ii) legal fees and expenses,`
  line
  line `(iii) any administration fees of the institution supervising the arbitration, and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other expenses incurred in connection with the arbitral proceedings and the arbitral`
  line award.
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 16, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for sub-section (8) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (24535)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 35
  title `Regime for costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s.17, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24535&sectionno=31A&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Regime for costs.-- (1) In relation to any arbitration proceeding or a proceeding under any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act pertaining to the arbitration, the Court or arbitral tribunal, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall have the discretion to`
  line determine--
  line
  line `(a) whether costs are payable by one party to another;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of such costs; and`
  line
  line `(c) when such costs are to be paid.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, "costs" means reasonable costs relating to--`
  line
  line `(i) the fees and expenses of the arbitrators, Courts and witnesses;`
  line
  line `(ii) legal fees and expenses;`
  line
  line `(iii) any administration fees of the institution supervising the arbitration; and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other expenses incurred in connection with the arbitral or Court proceedings and the`
  line `arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Court or arbitral tribunal decides to make an order as to payment of costs,`
  line
  line `(a) the general rule is that the unsuccessful party shall be ordered to pay the costs of the`
  line `successful party; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Court or arbitral tribunal may make a different order for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the costs, the Court or arbitral tribunal shall have regard to all the circumstances,`
  line including--
  line
  line `(a) the conduct of all the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) whether a party has succeeded partly in the case;`
  line
  line `(c) whether the party had made a frivolous counterclaim leading to delay in the disposal of the`
  line `arbitral proceedings; and`
  line
  line `(d) whether any reasonable offer to settle the dispute is made by a party and refused by the other`
  line party.
  line
  line `(4) The Court or arbitral tribunal may make any order under this section including the order that a`
  line `party shall pay--`
  line
  line `(a) a proportion of another party's costs;`
  line
  line `(b) a stated amount in respect of another party's costs;`
  line
  line `(c) costs from or until a certain date only;`
  line
  line `(d) costs incurred before proceedings have begun;`
  line
  line `(e) costs relating to particular steps taken in the proceedings;`
  line
  line `(f ) costs relating only to a distinct part of the proceedings; and`
  line
  line `(g) interest on costs from or until a certain date.`
  line
  line `(5) An agreement which has the effect that a party is to pay the whole or part of the costs of the`
  line `arbitration in any event shall be only valid if such agreement is made after the dispute in question has`
  line arisen.]
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (24536)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 36
  title `Termination of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24536&sectionno=32&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The arbitral proceedings shall be terminated by the final`
  line `arbitral award or by an order of the arbitral tribunal under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) The arbitral tribunal shall issue an order for the termination of the arbitral proceedings`
  line where—
  line
  line `(a) the claimant withdraws his claim, unless the respondent objects to the order and the`
  line `arbitral tribunal recognises a legitimate interest on his part in obtaining a final settlement of the`
  line dispute,
  line
  line `(b) the parties agree on the termination of the proceedings, or`
  line
  line `(c) the arbitral tribunal finds that the continuation of the proceedings has for any other reason`
  line `become unnecessary or impossible.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to section 33 and sub-section (4) of section 34, the mandate of the arbitral tribunal shall`
  line `terminate with the termination of the arbitral proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (24537)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 37
  title `Correction and interpretation of award; additional award.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24537&sectionno=33&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Within thirty days from the`
  line `receipt of the arbitral award, unless another period of time has been agreed upon by the parties—`
  line
  line `(a) a party, with notice to the other party, may request the arbitral tribunal to correct any`
  line `computation errors, any clerical or typographical errors or any other errors of a similar nature`
  line `occurring in the award;`
  line
  line `(b) if so agreed by the parties, a party, with notice to the other party, may request the arbitral`
  line `tribunal to give an interpretation of a specific point or part of the award.`
  line
  line `(2) If the arbitral tribunal considers the request made under sub-section (1) to be justified, it shall`
  line `make the correction or give the interpretation within thirty days from the receipt of the request and the`
  line `interpretation shall form part of the arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(3) The arbitral tribunal may correct any error of the type referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1),`
  line `on its own initiative, within thirty days from the date of the arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(4) Unless otherwise agreed by the parties, a party with notice to the other party, may request, within`
  line `thirty days from the receipt of the arbitral award, the arbitral tribunal to make an additional arbitral award`
  line `as to claims presented in the arbitral proceedings but omitted from the arbitral award.`
  line
  line `(5) If the arbitral tribunal considers the request made under sub-section (4) to be justified, it shall`
  line `make the additional arbitral award within sixty days from the receipt of such request.`
  line
  line `(6) The arbitral tribunal may extend, if necessary, the period of time within which it shall make a`
  line `correction, give an interpretation or make an additional arbitral award under sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `(7) Section 31 shall apply to a correction or interpretation of the arbitral award or to an additional`
  line `arbitral award made under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (24538)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 38
  title `Application for setting aside arbitral awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24538&sectionno=34&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Recourse to a Court against an arbitral award`
  line `may be made only by an application for setting aside such award in accordance with sub-section (2) and`
  line `sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(2) An arbitral award may be set aside by the Court only if--`
  line
  line `(a) the party making the application ^1[establishes on the basis of the record of the arbitral tribunal`
  line that]--
  line
  line `(i) a party was under some incapacity, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the arbitration agreement is not valid under the law to which the parties have subjected it`
  line `or, failing any indication thereon, under the law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) the party making the application was not given proper notice of the appointment of an`
  line `arbitrator or of the arbitral proceedings or was otherwise unable to present his case; or`
  line
  line `(iv) the arbitral award deals with a dispute not contemplated by or not falling within the terms`
  line `of the submission to arbitration, or it contains decisions on matters beyond the scope of the`
  line `submission to arbitration:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the decisions on matters submitted to arbitration can be separated from those`
  line `not so submitted, only that part of the arbitral award which contains decisions on matters not`
  line `submitted to arbitration may be set aside; or`
  line
  line `(v) the composition of the arbitral tribunal or the arbitral procedure was not in accordance`
  line `with the agreement of the parties, unless such agreement was in conflict with a provision of this`
  line `Part from which the parties cannot derogate, or, failing such agreement, was not in accordance`
  line `with this Part; or`
  line
  line `(b) the Court finds that--`
  line
  line `(i) the subject-matter of the dispute is not capable of settlement by arbitration under the law`
  line `for the time being in force, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the arbitral award is in conflict with the public policy of India.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation 1.--For the avoidance of any doubt, it is clarified that an award is in conflict with the`
  line `public policy of India, only if,--`
  line
  line `(i) the making of the award was induced or affected by fraud or corruption or was in violation`
  line `of section 75 or section 81; or`
  line
  line `(ii) it is in contravention with the fundamental policy of Indian law; or`
  line
  line `(iii) it is in conflict with the most basic notions of morality or justice.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--For the avoidance of doubt, the test as to whether there is a contravention with the`
  line `fundamental policy of Indian law shall not entail a review on the merits of the dispute.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) An arbitral award arising out of arbitrations other than international commercial arbitrations,`
  line `may also be set aside by the Court, if the Court finds that the award is vitiated by patent illegality`
  line `appearing on the face of the award:`
  line
  line `Provided that an award shall not be set aside merely on the ground of an erroneous application of the`
  line `law or by reappreciation of evidence.]`
  line
  line `(3) An application for setting aside may not be made after three months have elapsed from the date on`
  line `which the party making that application had received the arbitral award or, if a request had been made`
  line `under section 33, from the date on which that request had been disposed of by the arbitral tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Court is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause from`
  line `making the application within the said period of three months it may entertain the application within a`
  line `further period of thirty days, but not thereafter.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Court may, where it is appropriate and it is`
  line `so requested by a party, adjourn the proceedings for a period of time determined by it in order to give the`
  line `arbitral tribunal an opportunity to resume the arbitral proceedings or to take such other action as in the`
  line `opinion of arbitral tribunal will eliminate the grounds for setting aside the arbitral award.`
  line
  line `^3[(5) An application under this section shall be filed by a party only after issuing a prior notice to the`
  line `other party and such application shall be accompanied by an affidavit by the applicant endorsing`
  line `compliance with the said requirement.`
  line
  line `(6) An application under this section shall be disposed of expeditiously, and in any event, within a`
  line `period of one year from the date on which the notice referred to in sub-section (5) is served upon the other`
  line party.]
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Amendment of section 34.--`
  line
  line `(i) after sub-section (2), insert the following sub-section, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(2A) An arbitral award may also be set aside by the Court, if the Court finds that the award is`
  line `vitiated by patent illegality appearing on the face of the award:`
  line
  line `Provided that an award shall not be set aside merely on the ground of an erroneous application of`
  line `the law or by re-appreciation of evidence.";`
  line
  line `(ii) in sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(i) for "three months" substitute, "six months";`
  line
  line `(ii) in proviso thereto, for, "three months" and "thirty days" substitute respectively "six months"`
  line `and "sixty days".`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification`
  line `No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and Vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 7, for "furnishes proof that" (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 18, for the Explanation(w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (24539)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 39
  title `Finality of arbitral awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24539&sectionno=35&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `Subject to this Part an arbitral award shall be final and binding on`
  line `the parties and persons claiming under them respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (24540)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 40
  title Enforcement.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24540&sectionno=36&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `^1[36. Enforcement--(1) Where the time for making an application to set aside the arbitral award`
  line `under section 34 has expired, then, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), such award shall be`
  line `enforced in accordance with the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in the same`
  line `manner as if it were a decree of the court.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an application to set aside the arbitral award has been filed in the Court under section 34,`
  line `the filing of such an application shall not by itself render that award unenforceable, unless the Court`
  line `grants an order of stay of the operation of the said arbitral award in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3), on a separate application made for that purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon filing of an application under sub-section (2) for stay of the operation of the arbitral award,`
  line `the Court may, subject to such conditions as it may deem fit, grant stay of the operation of such award for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court shall, while considering the application for grant of stay in the case of an`
  line `arbitral award for payment of money, have due regard to the provisions for grant of stay of a money`
  line `decree under the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that where the Court is satisfied that a Prima facie case is made out that,--`
  line
  line `(a) the arbitration agreement or contract which is the basis of the award; or`
  line
  line `(b) the making of the award,`
  line
  line `was induced or effected by fraud or corruption, it shall stay the award unconditionally pending disposal of`
  line `the challenge under section 34 to the award.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the above proviso shall apply to`
  line `all court cases arising out of or in relation to arbitral proceedings, irrespective of whether the arbitral or`
  line `court proceedings were commenced prior to or after the commencement of the Arbitration and`
  line `Conciliation (Amendment) Act, 2015 (3 of 2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 19, ibid., for section 36 (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 2021, s. 2 (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (24541)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 41
  title `Appealable orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24541&sectionno=37&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, an appeal] shall lie from the following orders (and from no others) to the Court authorised`
  line `by law to hear appeals from original decrees of the Court passing the order, namely:--`
  line
  line `^2[(a) refusing to refer the parties to arbitration under section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) granting or refusing to grant any measure under section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) setting aside or refusing to set aside an arbitral award under section 34.]`
  line
  line `(2) Appeal shall also lie to a court from an order of the arbitral tribunal--`
  line
  line `(a) accepting the plea referred to in sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 16; or`
  line
  line `(b) granting or refusing to grant an interim measure under section 17.`
  line
  line `(3) No second appeal shall lie from an order passed in appeal under this section, but nothing in this`
  line `section shall affect or take away any right to appeal to the Supreme Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 8, for "An appeal" (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 20, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (24542)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 42
  title Deposits.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24542&sectionno=38&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The arbitral tribunal may fix the amount of the deposit or supplementary deposit,`
  line `as the case may be, as an advance for the costs referred to in sub-section (8) of section 31, which it`
  line `expects will be incurred in respect of the claim submitted to it:`
  line
  line `Provided that where, apart from the claim, a counter-claim has been submitted to the arbitral tribunal,`
  line `it may fix separate amount of deposit for the claim and counter-claim.`
  line
  line `(2) The deposit referred to in sub-section (1) shall be payable in equal shares by the parties:`
  line `Provided that where one party fails to pay his share of the deposit, the other party may pay that share:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the other party also does not pay the aforesaid share in respect of the`
  line `claim or the counter-claim, the arbitral tribunal may suspend or terminate the arbitral proceedings in`
  line `respect of such claim or counter-claim, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon termination of the arbitral proceedings, the arbitral tribunal shall render an accounting to the`
  line `parties of the deposits received and shall return any unexpended balance to the party or parties, as the case`
  line `may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (24543)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 43
  title `Lien on arbitral award and deposits as to costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24543&sectionno=39&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (2) and to any provision to the contrary in the arbitration agreement, the arbitral tribunal shall`
  line `have a lien on the arbitral award for any unpaid costs of the arbitration.`
  line
  line `(2) If in any case an arbitral tribunal refuses to deliver its award except on payment of the costs`
  line `demanded by it, the Court may, on an application in this behalf, order that the arbitral tribunal shall`
  line `deliver the arbitral award to the applicant on payment into Court by the applicant of the costs demanded,`
  line `and shall, after such inquiry, if any, as it thinks fit, further order that out of the money so paid into Court`
  line `there shall be paid to the arbitral tribunal by way of costs such sum as the Court may consider reasonable`
  line `and that the balance of the money, if any, shall be refunded to the applicant.`
  line
  line `(3) An application under sub-section (2) may be made by any party unless the fees demanded have`
  line `been fixed by written agreement between him and the arbitral tribunal, and the arbitral tribunal shall be`
  line `entitled to appear and be heard on any such application.`
  line
  line `(4) The Court may make such orders as it thinks fit respecting the costs of the arbitration where any`
  line `question arises respecting such costs and the arbitral award contains no sufficient provision concerning`
  line them.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (24544)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 44
  title `Arbitration agreement not to be discharged by death of party thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24544&sectionno=40&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) An arbitration`
  line `agreement shall not be discharged by the death of any party thereto either as respects the deceased or as`
  line `respects any other party, but shall in such event be enforceable by or against the legal representative of`
  line `the deceased.`
  line
  line `(2) The mandate of an arbitrator shall not be terminated by the death of any party by whom he was`
  line appointed.
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall affect the operation of any law by virtue of which any right of action`
  line `is extinguished by the death of a person.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (24545)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 45
  title `Provisions in case of insolvency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24545&sectionno=41&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it is provided by a term in a contract to which an`
  line `insolvent is a party that any dispute arising thereout or in connection therewith shall be submitted to`
  line `arbitration, the said term shall, if the receiver adopts the contract, be enforceable by or against him so far`
  line `as it relates to any such dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person who has been adjudged an insolvent had, before the commencement of the`
  line `insolvency proceedings, become a party to an arbitration agreement, and any matter to which the`
  line `agreement applies is required to be determined in connection with, or for the purposes of, the insolvency`
  line `proceedings, then, if the case is one to which sub-section (1) does not apply, any other party or the`
  line `receiver may apply to the judicial authority having jurisdiction in the insolvency proceedings for an order`
  line `directing that the matter in question shall be submitted to arbitration in accordance with the arbitration`
  line `agreement, and the judicial authority may, if it is of opinion that, having regard to all the circumstances of`
  line `the case, the matter ought to be determined by arbitration, make an order accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) In this section the expression "receiver" includes an Official Assignee.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (24546)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 46
  title Jurisdiction.
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24546&sectionno=42&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained elsewhere in this Part or in any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, where with respect to an arbitration agreement any application under this Part has`
  line `been made in a Court, that Court alone shall have jurisdiction over the arbitral proceedings and all sequent applications arising out of that agreement and the arbitral proceedings shall be made in that`
  line `Court and in no other Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42_a:
  sectionId (49518)
  sectionNo 42A
  orderNo 47
  title `Confidentiality of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 9 (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=49518&sectionno=42A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_42_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[42A. Confidentiality of information.-- Notwithstanding anything contained by any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, the arbitrator, the arbitral institution and the parties to the arbitration agreement`
  line `shall maintain confidentially of all arbitral proceedings except award where its disclosure is necessary for`
  line `the purpose of implementation and enforcement of award.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42_b:
  sectionId (49519)
  sectionNo 42B
  orderNo 48
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 9 (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=49519&sectionno=42B&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_42_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[42B. Protection of action taken in good faith.-- No suit or other legal proceedings shall lie against`
  line `the arbitrator for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (24547)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 49
  title Limitations.
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24547&sectionno=43&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), shall apply to arbitrations as it applies`
  line `to proceedings in court.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section and the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), an arbitration shall be`
  line `deemed to have commenced on the date referred to in section 21.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an arbitration agreement to submit future disputes to arbitration provides that any claim to`
  line `which the agreement applies shall be barred unless some step to commence arbitral proceedings is taken`
  line `within a time fixed by the agreement, and a dispute arises to which the agreement applies, the Court, if it`
  line `is of opinion that in the circumstances of the case undue hardship would otherwise be caused, and`
  line `notwithstanding that the time so fixed has expired, may on such terms, if any, as the justice of the case`
  line `may require, extend the time for such period as it thinks proper.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Court orders that an arbitral award be set aside, the period between the commencement`
  line `of the arbitration and the date of the order of the Court shall be excluded in computing the time prescribed`
  line `by the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963), for the commencement of the proceedings (including`
  line `arbitration) with respect to the dispute so submitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
