obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (24548)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 63
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24548&sectionno=44&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, "foreign award" means an`
  line `arbitral award on differences between persons arising out of legal relationships, whether contractual or`
  line `not, considered as commercial under the law in force in India, made on or after the 11th day of`
  line `October, 1960—`
  line
  line `(a) in pursuance of an agreement in writing for arbitration to which the Convention set forth in`
  line `the First Schedule applies, and`
  line
  line `(b) in one of such territories as the Central Government, being satisfied that reciprocal provisions`
  line `have been made may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be territories to which the said`
  line `Convention applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (24549)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 64
  title `Power of judicial authority to refer parties to arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 11, for "unless it finds" (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24549&sectionno=45&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in Part I`
  line `or in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), a judicial authority, when seized of an action in a matter in`
  line `respect of which the parties have made an agreement referred to in section 44, shall, at the request of one of the`
  line `parties or any person claiming through or under him, refer the parties to arbitration, ^1[unless it prima facie finds] that`
  line `the said agreement is null and void, inoperative or incapable of being performed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (24550)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 65
  title `When foreign award binding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24550&sectionno=46&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Any foreign award which would be enforceable under this`
  line `Chapter shall be treated as binding for all purposes on the persons as between whom it was made, and`
  line `may accordingly be relied on by any of those persons by way of defence, set off or otherwise in any legal`
  line `proceedings in India and any references in this Chapter to enforcing a foreign award shall be construed as`
  line `including references to relying on an award.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (24551)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 66
  title Evidence.
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 21, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24551&sectionno=47&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The party applying for the enforcement of a foreign award shall, at the time of the`
  line `application, produce before the court—`
  line
  line `(a) the original award or a copy thereof, duly authenticated in the manner required by the law of`
  line `the country in which it was made;`
  line
  line `(b) the original agreement for arbitration or a duly certified copy thereof; and`
  line
  line `(c) such evidence as may be necessary to prove that the award is a foreign award.`
  line
  line `(2) If the award or agreement to be produced under sub-section (1) is in a foreign language, the party`
  line `seeking to enforce the award shall produce a translation into English certified as correct by a diplomatic or consular agent of the country to which that party belongs or certified as correct in such other manner as`
  line `may be sufficient according to the law in force in India.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.—In this section and in the sections following in this Chapter, "Court" means the High`
  line `Court having original jurisdiction to decide the questions forming the subject-matter of the arbitral award`
  line `if the same had been the subject-matter of a suit on its original civil jurisdiction and in other cases, in the`
  line `High Court having jurisdiction to hear appeals from decrees of courts subordinate to such High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (24552)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 67
  title `Conditions for enforcement of foreign awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 22, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24552&sectionno=48&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Enforcement of a foreign award may be`
  line `refused, at the request of the party against whom it is invoked, only if that party furnishes to the court`
  line `proof that—`
  line
  line `(a) the parties to the agreement referred to in section 44 were, under the law applicable to them,`
  line `under some incapacity, or the said agreement is not valid under the law to which the parties have`
  line `subjected it or, failing any indication thereon, under the law of the country where the award was`
  line `made; or`
  line
  line `(b) the party against whom the award is invoked was not given proper notice of the appointment`
  line `of the arbitrator or of the arbitral proceedings or was otherwise unable to present his case; or`
  line
  line `(c) the award deals with a difference not contemplated by or not falling within the terms of the`
  line `submission to arbitration, or it contains decisions on matters beyond the scope of the submission to`
  line `arbitration:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the decisions on matters submitted to arbitration can be separated from those not`
  line `so submitted, that part of the award which contains decisions on matters submitted to arbitration may`
  line `be enforced; or`
  line
  line `(d) the composition of the arbitral authority or the arbitral procedure was not in accordance with`
  line `the agreement of the parties, or, failing such agreement, was not in accordance with the law of the`
  line `country where the arbitration took place ; or`
  line
  line `(e) the award has not yet become binding on the parties, or has been set aside or suspended by a`
  line `competent authority of the country in which, or under the law of which, that award was made.`
  line
  line `(2) Enforcement of an arbitral award may also be refused if the Court finds that—`
  line
  line `(a) the subject-matter of the difference is not capable of settlement by arbitration under the`
  line `law of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) the enforcement of the award would be contrary to the public policy of India.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation 1.—For the avoidance of any doubt, it is clarified that an award is in conflict with the`
  line `public policy of India, only if,—`
  line
  line `(i) the making of the award was induced or affected by fraud or corruption or was in violation of`
  line `section 75 or section 81; or`
  line
  line `(ii) it is in contravention with the fundamental policy of Indian law; or`
  line
  line `(iii) it is in conflict with the most basic notions of morality or justice.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—For the avoidance of doubt, the test as to whether there is a contravention with the`
  line `fundamental policy of Indian law shall not entail a review on the merits of the dispute.]`
  line
  line `(3) If an application for the setting aside or suspension of the award has been made to a competent`
  line `authority referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) the Court may, if it considers it proper, adjourn the`
  line `decision on the enforcement of the award and may also, on the application of the party claiming`
  line `enforcement of the award, order the other party to give suitable security.`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (24553)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 68
  title `Enforcement of foreign awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24553&sectionno=49&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Where the Court is satisfied that the foreign award is`
  line `enforceable under this Chapter, the award shall be deemed to be a decree of that Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (24554)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 69
  title `Appealable orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 12, for "An appeal" (w.e.f. 30-8-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24554&sectionno=50&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, an appeal] shall lie from the order refusing to--`
  line
  line `(a) refer the parties to arbitration under section 45;`
  line
  line `(b) enforce a foreign award under section 48,`
  line
  line `to the court authorised by law to hear appeals from such order.`
  line
  line `(2) No second appeal shall lie from an order passed in appeal under this section, but nothing in this`
  line `section shall affect or take away any right to appeal to the Supreme Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (24555)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 70
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24555&sectionno=51&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall prejudice any rights which any person would have had of`
  line `enforcing in India of any award or of availing himself in India of any award if this Chapter had not been`
  line enacted.
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (24556)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 71
  title `Chapter II not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24556&sectionno=52&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `Chapter II of this Part shall not apply in relation to foreign awards to`
  line `which this Chapter applies.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (24557)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 72
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24557&sectionno=53&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter "foreign award" means an arbitral award on differences relating`
  line `to matters considered as commercial under the law in force in India made after the 28th day of July,`
  line 1924,—
  line
  line `(a) in pursuance of an agreement for arbitration to which the Protocol set forth in the Second`
  line `Schedule applies, and`
  line
  line `(b) between persons of whom one is subject to the jurisdiction of some one of such Powers as the`
  line `Central Government, being satisfied that reciprocal provisions have been made, may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, declare to be parties to the Convention set forth in the Third Schedule, and of`
  line `whom the other is subject to the jurisdiction of some other of the Powers aforesaid, and`
  line
  line `(c) in one of such territories as the Central Government, being satisfied that reciprocal provisions`
  line `have been made, may, by like notification, declare to be territories to which the said Convention`
  line applies,
  line
  line `and for the purposes of this Chapter an award shall not be deemed to be final if any proceedings for the`
  line `purpose of contesting the validity of the award are pending in the country in which it was made.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (24558)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power of judicial authority to refer parties to arbitration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24558&sectionno=54&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in Part I or in the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), a judicial authority, on being`
  line `seized of a dispute regarding a contract made between persons to whom section 53 applies and including`
  line `an arbitration agreement, whether referring to present or future differences, which is valid under that`
  line `section and capable of being carried into effect, shall refer the parties on the application of either of them`
  line `or any person claiming through or under him to the decision of the arbitrators and such reference shall not`
  line `prejudice the competence of the judicial authority in case the agreement or the arbitration cannot proceed`
  line `or becomes inoperative.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (24559)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 74
  title `Foreign awards when binding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24559&sectionno=55&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `Any foreign award which would be enforceable under this`
  line `Chapter shall be treated as binding for all purposes on the persons as between whom it was made, and`
  line `may accordingly be relied on by any of those persons by way of defence, set off or otherwise in any legal`
  line `proceedings in India and any references in this Chapter to enforcing a foreign award shall be construed as`
  line `including references to relying on an award.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (24560)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 75
  title Evidence.
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 2016, s. 23, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24560&sectionno=56&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) The party applying for the enforcement of a foreign award shall, at the time of`
  line `application produce before the Court—`
  line
  line `(a) the original award or a copy thereof duly authenticated in the manner required by the law of`
  line `the country in which it was made;`
  line
  line `(b) evidence proving that the award has become final; and`
  line
  line `(c) such evidence as may be necessary to prove that the conditions mentioned in`
  line `clauses (a) and (c) of sub-section (1) of section 57 are satisfied.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any document requiring to be produced under sub-section (1) is in a foreign language, the`
  line `party seeking to enforce the award shall produce a translation into English certified as correct by a`
  line `diplomatic or consular agent of the country to which that party belongs or certified as correct in such`
  line `other manner as may be sufficient according to the law in force in India.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.—In this section and in the sections following in this Chapter, "Court" means the High`
  line `Court having original jurisdiction to decide the questions forming the subject-matter of the arbitral award`
  line `if the same had been the subject-matter of a suit on its original civil jurisdiction and in other cases, in the`
  line `High Court having jurisdiction to hear appeals from decrees of courts subordinate to such High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (24561)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 76
  title `Conditions for enforcement of foreign awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 24, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24561&sectionno=57&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) In order that a foreign award may be`
  line `enforceable under this Chapter, it shall be necessary that—`
  line
  line `(a) the award has been made in pursuance of a submission to arbitration which is valid under the`
  line `law applicable thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) the subject-matter of the award is capable of settlement by arbitration under the law of India;`
  line
  line `(c) the award has been made by the arbitral tribunal provided for in the submission to arbitration`
  line `or constituted in the manner agreed upon by the parties and in conformity with the law governing the`
  line `arbitration procedure;`
  line
  line `(d) the award has become final in the country in which it has been made, in the sense that it will`
  line `not be considered as such if it is open to opposition or appeal or if it is proved that any proceedings`
  line `for the purpose of contesting the validity of the award are pending;`
  line
  line `(e) the enforcement of the award is not contrary to the public policy or the law of India.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation 1.—For the avoidance of any doubt, it is clarified that an award is in conflict with the`
  line `public policy of India, only if,—`
  line
  line `(i) the making of the award was induced or affected by fraud or corruption or was in violation of`
  line `section 75 or section 81; or`
  line
  line `(ii) it is in contravention with the fundamental policy of Indian law; or`
  line
  line `(iii) it is in conflict with the most basic notions of morality or justice.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.—For the avoidance of doubt, the test as to whether there is a contravention with the`
  line `fundamental policy of Indian law shall not entail a review on the merits of the dispute.]`
  line
  line `(2) Even if the conditions laid down in sub-section (1) are fulfilled, enforcement of the award shall be`
  line `refused if the Court is satisfied that—`
  line
  line `(a) the award has been annulled in the country in which it was made;`
  line
  line `(b) the party against whom it is sought to use the award was not given notice of the`
  line `arbitration proceedings in sufficient time to enable him to present his case; or that, being under a`
  line `legal incapacity, he was not properly represented;`
  line
  line `(c) the award does not deal with the differences contemplated by or falling within the terms`
  line `of the submission to arbitration or that it contains decisions on matters beyond the scope of the`
  line `submission to arbitration:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the award has not covered all the differences submitted to the arbitral tribunal, the`
  line `Court may, if it thinks fit, postpone such enforcement or grant it subject to such guarantee as the Court`
  line `may decide.`
  line
  line `(3) If the party against whom the award has been made proves that under the law governing the`
  line `arbitration procedure there is a ground, other than the grounds referred to in clauses (a) and (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) and clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (2) entitling him to contest the validity of the award,`
  line `the Court may, if it thinks fit, either refuse enforcement of the award or adjourn the consideration thereof,`
  line `giving such party a reasonable time within which to have the award annulled by the competent tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (24562)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 77
  title `Enforcement of foreign awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24562&sectionno=58&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Where the Court is satisfied that the foreign award is`
  line `enforceable under this Chapter, the award shall be deemed to be a decree of the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (24563)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 78
  title `Appealable orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24563&sectionno=59&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie from the order refusing—`
  line
  line `(a) to refer the parties to arbitration under section 54; and`
  line
  line `(b) to enforce a foreign award under section 57,`
  line
  line `to the court authorised by law to hear appeals from such order.`
  line
  line `(2) No second appeal shall lie from an order passed in appeal under this section, but nothing in this`
  line `section shall affect or take away any right to appeal to the Supreme Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (24564)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 79
  title Savings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24564&sectionno=60&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Chapter shall prejudice any rights which any person would have had of`
  line `enforcing in India of any award or of availing himself in India of any award if this Chapter had not been`
  line enacted.
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (24565)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 80
  title `Application and scope.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24565&sectionno=61&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided by any law for the time being in force`
  line `and unless the parties have otherwise agreed, this Part shall apply to conciliation of disputes arising out of`
  line `legal relationship, whether contractual or not and to all proceedings relating thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) This Part shall not apply where by virtue of any law for the time being in force certain disputes`
  line `may not be submitted to conciliation.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (24566)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 81
  title `Commencement of conciliation proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24566&sectionno=62&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) The party initiating conciliation shall send to`
  line `the other party a written invitation to conciliate under this Part, briefly identifying the subject of the`
  line dispute.
  line
  line `(2) Conciliation proceedings, shall commence when the other party accepts in writing the invitation to`
  line conciliate.
  line
  line `(3) If the other party rejects the invitation, there will be no conciliation proceedings.`
  line
  line `(4) If the party initiating conciliation does not receive a reply within thirty days from the date on`
  line `which he sends the invitation, or within such other period of time as specified in the invitation, he may`
  line `elect to treat this as a rejection of the invitation to conciliate and if he so elects, he shall inform in writing`
  line `the other party accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (24567)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 82
  title `Number of conciliators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24567&sectionno=63&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be one conciliator unless the parties agree that there`
  line `shall be two or three conciliators.`
  line
  line `(2) Where there is more than one conciliator, they ought, as a general rule, to act jointly.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (24568)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 83
  title `Appointment of conciliators.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24568&sectionno=64&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to sub-section (2)—`
  line
  line `(a) in conciliation proceedings, with one conciliator, the parties may agree on the name of a sole`
  line conciliator;
  line
  line `(b) in conciliation proceedings with two conciliators, each party may appoint one conciliator;`
  line
  line `(c) in conciliation proceedings with three conciliators, each party may appoint one conciliator and`
  line `the parties may agree on the name of the third conciliator who shall act as the presiding conciliator.`
  line
  line `(2) Parties may enlist the assistance of a suitable institution or person in connection with the`
  line `appointment of conciliators, and in particular,—`
  line
  line `(a) a party may request such an institution or person to recommend the names of suitable`
  line `individuals to act as conciliator; or`
  line
  line `(b) the parties may agree that the appointment of one or more conciliators be made directly by`
  line `such an institution or person:`
  line
  line `Provided that in recommending or appointing individuals to act as conciliator, the institution or`
  line `person shall have regard to such considerations as are likely to secure the appointment of an independent and impartial conciliator and, with respect to a sole or third conciliator, shall take into account the`
  line `advisability of appointing a conciliator of a nationality other than the nationalities of the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (24569)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 84
  title `Submission of statements to conciliator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24569&sectionno=65&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conciliator, upon his appointment, may`
  line `request each party to submit to him a brief written statement describing the general nature of the dispute`
  line `and the points at issue. Each party shall send a copy of such statement to the other party.`
  line
  line `(2) The conciliator may request each party to submit to him a further written statement of his position`
  line `and the facts and grounds in support thereof, supplemented by any documents and other evidence that`
  line `such party deems appropriate. The party shall send a copy of such statement, documents and other`
  line `evidence to the other party.`
  line
  line `(3) At any stage of the conciliation proceedings, the conciliator may request a party to submit to him`
  line `such additional information as he deems appropriate.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—In this section and all the following sections of this Part, the term "conciliator" applies`
  line `to a sole conciliator, two or three conciliators, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (24570)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 85
  title `Conciliator not bound by certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24570&sectionno=66&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `The conciliator is not bound by the Code of`
  line `Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) or the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (24571)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 86
  title `Role of conciliator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24571&sectionno=67&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conciliator shall assist the parties in an independent and impartial`
  line `manner in their attempt to reach an amicable settlement of their dispute.`
  line
  line `(2) The conciliator shall be guided by principles of objectivity, fairness and justice, giving`
  line `consideration to, among other things, the rights and obligations of the parties, the usages of the trade`
  line `concerned and the circumstances surrounding the dispute, including any previous business practices`
  line `between the parties.`
  line
  line `(3) The conciliator may conduct the conciliation proceedings in such a manner as he considers`
  line `appropriate, taking into account the circumstances of the case, the wishes the parties may express,`
  line `including any request by a party that the conciliator hear oral statements, and the need for a speedy`
  line `settlement of the dispute.`
  line
  line `(4) The conciliator may, at any stage of the conciliation proceedings, make proposals for a settlement`
  line `of the dispute. Such proposals need not be in writing and need not be accompanied by a statement of the`
  line `reasons therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (24572)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 87
  title `Administrative assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24572&sectionno=68&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `In order to facilitate the conduct of the conciliation proceedings, the`
  line `parties, or the conciliator with the consent of the parties, may arrange for administrative assistance by a`
  line `suitable institution or person.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (24573)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 88
  title `Communication between conciliator and parties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24573&sectionno=69&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conciliator may invite the parties to`
  line `meet him or may communicate with them orally or in writing. He may meet or communicate with the`
  line `parties together or with each of them separately.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless the parties have agreed upon the place where meetings with the conciliator are to be held,`
  line `such place shall be determined by the conciliator, after consultation with the parties, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances of the conciliation proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (24574)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 89
  title `Disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24574&sectionno=70&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `When the conciliator receives factual information concerning the`
  line `dispute from a party, he shall disclose the substance of that information to the other party in order that the`
  line `other party may have the opportunity to present any explanation which he considers appropriate:`
  line
  line `Provided that when a party gives any information to the conciliator subject to a specific condition that`
  line `it be kept confidential, the conciliator shall not disclose that information to the other party.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (24575)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 90
  title `Co-operation of parties with conciliator.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24575&sectionno=71&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `The parties shall in good faith co-operate with the`
  line `conciliator and, in particular, shall endeavour to comply with requests by the conciliator to submit written`
  line `materials, provide evidence and attend meetings.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (24576)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 91
  title `Suggestions by parties for settlement of dispute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24576&sectionno=72&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `Each party may, on his own initiative or at`
  line `the invitation of the conciliator, submit to the conciliator suggestions for the settlement of the dispute.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (24577)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 92
  title `Settlement agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24577&sectionno=73&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `(1) When it appears to the conciliator that there exist elements of a`
  line `settlement which may be acceptable to the parties, he shall formulate the terms of a possible settlement`
  line `and submit them to the parties for their observations. After receiving the observations of the parties, the`
  line `conciliator may reformulate the terms of a possible settlement in the light of such observations.`
  line
  line `(2) If the parties reach agreement on a settlement of the dispute, they may draw up and sign a written`
  line `settlement agreement. If requested by the parties, the conciliator may draw up, or assist the parties in`
  line `drawing up, the settlement agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) When the parties sign the settlement agreement, it shall be final and binding on the parties and`
  line `persons claiming under them respectively.`
  line
  line `(4) The conciliator shall authenticate the settlement agreement and furnish a copy thereof to each of`
  line `the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (24578)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 93
  title `Status and effect of settlement agreement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24578&sectionno=74&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `The settlement agreement shall have the same`
  line `status and effect as if it is an arbitral award on agreed terms on the substance of the dispute rendered by`
  line `an arbitral tribunal under section 30.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (24579)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 94
  title Confidentiality.
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24579&sectionno=75&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the conciliator and the parties shall keep confidential all matters relating to the conciliation`
  line `proceedings. Confidentiality shall extend also to the settlement agreement, except where its disclosure is`
  line `necessary for purposes of implementation and enforcement.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (24580)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 95
  title `Termination of conciliation proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24580&sectionno=76&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `The conciliation proceedings shall be terminated—`
  line
  line `(a) by the signing of the settlement agreement by the parties, on the date of the agreement; or`
  line
  line `(b) by a written declaration of the conciliator, after consultation with the parties, to the effect that`
  line `further efforts at conciliation are no longer justified, on the date of the declaration; or`
  line
  line `(c) by a written declaration of the parties addressed to the conciliator to the effect that the`
  line `conciliation proceedings are terminated, on the date of the declaration; or`
  line
  line `(d) by a written declaration of a party to the other party and the conciliator, if appointed, to the`
  line `effect that the conciliation proceedings are terminated, on the date of the declaration.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (24581)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 96
  title `Resort to arbitral or judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24581&sectionno=77&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The parties shall not initiate, during the`
  line `conciliation proceedings, any arbitral or judicial proceedings in respect of a dispute that is the`
  line `subject-matter of the conciliation proceedings except that a party may initiate arbitral or judicial`
  line `proceedings where, in his opinion, such proceedings are necessary for preserving his rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (24582)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 97
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24582&sectionno=78&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `(1) Upon termination of the conciliation proceedings, the conciliator shall fix the costs of`
  line `the conciliation and give written notice thereof to the parties.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of sub-section (1), "costs" means reasonable costs relating to—`
  line
  line `(a) the fee and expenses of the conciliator and witnesses requested by the conciliator with the`
  line `consent of the parties;`
  line
  line `(b) any expert advice requested by the conciliator with the consent of the parties;`
  line
  line `(c) any assistance provided pursuant to clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 64 and section 68.`
  line
  line `(d) any other expenses incurred in connection with the conciliation proceedings and the`
  line `settlement agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) The costs shall be borne equally by the parties unless the settlement agreement provides for a`
  line `different apportionment. All other expenses incurred by a party shall be borne by that party.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (24583)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 98
  title Deposits.
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24583&sectionno=79&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) The conciliator may direct each party to deposit an equal amount as an advance`
  line `for the costs referred to in sub-section (2) of section 78 which he expects will be incurred.`
  line
  line `(2) During the course of the conciliation proceedings, the conciliator may direct supplementary`
  line `deposits in an equal amount from each party.`
  line
  line `(3) If the required deposits under sub-sections (1) and (2) are not paid in full by both parties within`
  line `thirty days, the conciliator may suspend the proceedings or may make a written declaration of termination`
  line `of the proceedings to the parties, effective on the date of that declaration.`
  line
  line `(4) Upon termination of the conciliation proceedings, the conciliator shall render an accounting to the`
  line `parties of the deposits received and shall return any unexpended balance to the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (24584)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 99
  title `Role of conciliator in other proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24584&sectionno=80&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `Unless otherwise agreed by the parties,—`
  line
  line `(a) the conciliator shall not act as an arbitrator or as a representative or counsel of a party in any`
  line `arbitral or judicial proceeding in respect of a dispute that is the subject of the conciliation`
  line proceedings;
  line
  line `(b) the conciliator shall not be presented by the parties as a witness in any arbitral or judicial`
  line proceedings.
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (24585)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 100
  title `Admissibility of evidence in other proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24585&sectionno=81&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `The parties shall not rely on or introduce as`
  line `evidence in arbitral or judicial proceedings, whether or not such proceedings relate to the dispute that is`
  line `the subject of the conciliation proceedings,—`
  line
  line `(a) views expressed or suggestions made by the other party in respect of a possible settlement of`
  line `the dispute;`
  line
  line `(b) admissions made by the other party in the course of the conciliation proceedings;`
  line
  line `(c) proposals made by the conciliator;`
  line
  line `(d) the fact that the other party had indicated his willingness to accept a proposal for settlement`
  line `made by the conciliator.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (24586)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 101
  title `Power of High Court to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24586&sectionno=82&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may make rules consistent with this Act`
  line `as to all proceedings before the Court under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (24587)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 102
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24587&sectionno=83&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this Act,`
  line `the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall made be after the expiry of a period of two years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (24588)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 103
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24588&sectionno=84&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after`
  line `it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (24589)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 104
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24589&sectionno=85&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Arbitration (Protocol and Convention) Act, 1937 (6 of 1937), the`
  line `Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940) and the Foreign Awards (Recognition and Enforcement)`
  line `Act, 1961 (45 of 1961) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,—`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of the said enactments shall apply in relation to arbitral proceedings which`
  line `commenced before this Act came into force unless otherwise agreed by the parties but this Act shall`
  line `apply in relation to arbitral proceedings which commenced on or after this Act comes into force;`
  line
  line `(b) all rules made and notifications published, under the said enactments shall, to the extent to`
  line `which they are not repugnant to this Act, be deemed respectively to have been made or issued under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (24590)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 105
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=24590&sectionno=86&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Arbitration and Conciliation (Third) Ordinance, 1996 (Ord. 27 of`
  line `1996) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, any order, rule, notification or scheme made or anything done or`
  line `any action taken in pursuance of any provision of the said Ordinance shall be deemed to have been`
  line `made, done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (49520)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 106
  title `Effect of arbitral and related court proceedings commenced prior to 23rd October, 2015.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 33 of 2019, s. 13 (w.e.f. 23-10-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919&sectionId=49520&sectionno=87&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00004_199626_1517807323919
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `^1[87. Effect of arbitral and related court proceedings commenced.-- Unless the parties otherwise`
  line `agree, the amendments made to this Act by the Arbitration and Conciliation (Amendment) Act, 2015`
  line shall--
  line
  line `(a) not apply to--`
  line
  line `(i) arbitral proceedings commenced before the commencement of the Arbitration and Conciliation`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2015 (23rd October, 2015);`
  line
  line `(ii) court proceedings arising out of or in relation to such arbitral proceedings irrespective of`
  line `whether such court proceedings are commenced prior to or after the commencement of the`
  line `Arbitration and Conciliation (Amendment) Act, 2015;`
  line
  line `(b) apply only to arbitral proceedings commenced on or after the commencement of the Arbitration`
  line `and Conciliation (Amendment) Act, 2015 and to court proceedings arising out of or in relation to such`
  line `arbitral proceedings.]`
